      "originalNumber": 100
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "f02bebd3914384dd81b9a789db6834a9f0877205",
    "explanation": "The seven OSI layers are Physical, Data Link, Network, Transport, Session, Presentation and Application. 'Communication' is not one of them, so it is the odd one out."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q101",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "network-tools",
    "stem": "Which one of the following is used to display the configuration settings for the host:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "ipconfig",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "ping",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "snmp",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "route",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 101
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "858c8ab6b232e9bfa82d8c823db8808bad5abc31",
    "explanation": "ipconfig (ifconfig or ip on UNIX) prints the host's own configuration: IP address, subnet mask and default gateway. ping only tests reachability of another host, route shows the routing table, and SNMP is a management protocol rather than a host command."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q102",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "ip-addressing",
    "stem": "The IP address consists of two parts:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Gateway ID and Network ID",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Network ID and Host ID",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "MAC Address ID and Host ID",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "Subnet ID and Network ID",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 102
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "b88f9f5204fb64f5414dba292667781736216577",
    "explanation": "The subnet mask splits an IP address into a network ID (which network the host is on) and a host ID (which machine on that network). The MAC address is a separate layer 2 identifier and is not part of the IP address."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q103",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "software-engineering",
    "subtopic": "project-management",
    "stem": "What are the phases of a project life cycle in order?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Define the project, Plan the project, Get approval/decision to proceed, Implement the project plan and evaluate the project.",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Plan the project, Get approval/ decision to proceed, define the project, Implement the project plan and evaluate the project.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "Evaluate the project, Get approval/ decision to proceed, Plan the project, Define the project and Implement the project plan.",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 103
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "03806fe2c295bb2ce77b4dba4f83578c6b049d78",
    "explanation": "The order is define, plan, get approval, implement, evaluate: you cannot plan what is not yet defined, approval gates spending on implementation, and evaluation only makes sense after delivery. B plans before defining and C evaluates before the project exists."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q104",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "number-systems",
    "subtopic": "units",
    "stem": "A Terabyte is less than:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "One Petabyte",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "One Thousand Megabytes",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "One Hundred Gigabytes",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "One Million Kilobytes",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
